{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"CONTAINER review (G4 — child consistency), parent c81c (plan-review fan-out optimization). Checked the 7 cross-child interaction modes for this child (S5 bin-packing) against the whole sibling roster (S1 0250, S2 c6e5, S3 ba7e, S4 98c6, S6 da34) and the parent. NO G4 FINDINGS.\n\nAffirmations:\n- Implicit shared state: the `sizing.py` container-cost projection (`len(cont)*n_children*COST_AGENT_USD`, sizing.py:206) is touched by THREE siblings in sequence — S3 (fix base cost model + \"container never shed\"), S4 (2N->N), S5 (this child: <N after packing). This is real shared state, but it is EXPLICITLY ordering-resolved by the parent's Sequencing note (\"Land S3 -> S4 -> S5 STRICTLY in DAG order: S4/S5's sizing.py container-cost projections are only correct AFTER S3's 'container never shed' + cost-model fix lands\") and the DAG (S3->S4->S5). Each landing layers a correct projection on the prior. No contradiction.\n- Conflicting assumptions: S5's \"Why\" (\"After merge, the container still makes one call per child\") correctly assumes S4 has landed — matches the DAG. The ca03 \"each child WHOLE / never chunked\" window-fit invariant is upheld consistently with the parent's Out-of-scope (chunking forbidden) and S4's same invariant. No conflict.\n- Dependency gap: S5's incoming deps are correctly modeled as `blocks` links on the blockers — S4 (98c6) blocks 1762 and S6 (da34) blocks 1762 — matching the parent DAG `S4->S5` and `S6->{S4,S5}`. S5's fidelity gate is the S6 semantic harness (DEPENDS ON S6), correctly declared. No gap.\n- Scope overlap: S4 and S5 both edit `plan_review_container.md` (prompt) and `sizing.py` (projection). Because S4->S5 is strict, these are SERIAL layered edits (S4 adds the dual-rubric/attribution; S5 adds multi-child sections + required per-child output; S5 takes the sizing projection from N to <N), not concurrent contradictory ownership. The strict-ordering Sequencing note governs the sizing.py seam. Benign under ANTI-FP.\n- Ordering violation: none — S5 is the terminal node of the strict S3->S4->S5 chain and is the last to touch the shared projection.\n- Consumer impact: S5's bin-packer reshapes the `_run_container` call structure produced by S3's new pool + warm-then-fan-out, consuming (not contradicting) S3's \"container criteria NEVER shed\" guarantee. Producer->consumer is DAG-ordered. Consistent.\n- Residual references: S5 preserves the EXISTING single-child fallback and the \"too-big -> reduce the ticket\" failure finding as unchanged behavior — consistent with the parent's ca03 window-fit guarantee; no sibling carries a stale contract against a design S5 removes.\n\nCross-child note (not a finding; consistency-positive): the S6/S4/S5 shared comment flags that the REQUIRED structured per-child output guardrail \"already in S5\" must ALSO apply to S4 and that S6's eval should check TAIL-child recall — this is an S4/S6 obligation, not an S5 gap; S5 already carries the guardrail and the eval-gate dependency. No G4 inconsistency for this pairing."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782577558647768001,"uuid":"c97f4966-67e5-45bc-891c-fa4f820b0711"}